==============================================================
    CHAIN OF THOUGHT PROMPTING - A SIMPLE GUIDE
==============================================================

WHAT IS THIS?
-------------
A cheat sheet of keywords that make AI give better, more 
logical answers — especially for coding and reasoning tasks.


WHY DO KEYWORDS MATTER?
-----------------------
Instead of saying: "Fix my code"
Say: "Fix my code. Think step by step and explain your reasoning."

The AI slows down, thinks carefully, and gives better answers.


==============================================================
                    THE 8 KEYWORD CATEGORIES
==============================================================

1. ROLE KEYWORDS
----------------
Purpose: Tells the AI WHO to pretend to be.

Keywords:
  • "Act as a senior Java developer"
  • "Act as a Spring Boot expert"
  • "Act as a code reviewer"
  • "Act as a performance optimization expert"

Example:
  "Act as a senior Java developer and Spring Batch expert."


2. CODE GENERATION KEYWORDS
---------------------------
Purpose: Asks the AI to WRITE NEW CODE.

Keywords:
  • "Generate Java code that..."
  • "Implement a method that..."
  • "Write a class that..."
  • "Use clean, idiomatic Java"
  • "Follow SOLID principles"
  • "Avoid unnecessary complexity"

Example:
  "Generate Java code that implements this logic and use 
   clean, idiomatic Java."


3. CHAIN-OF-THOUGHT KEYWORDS (MOST IMPORTANT!)
----------------------------------------------
Purpose: Forces the AI to THINK BEFORE ANSWERING.

The Golden Phrase:
  >>> "Let's think step by step." <<<

Other Keywords:
  • "First outline the approach, then write the code"
  • "Explain your reasoning before showing the code"
  • "Break the solution into clear steps"
  • "Identify edge cases before coding"
  • "Show your work"

Example:
  "Think step by step before writing code and identify 
   edge cases before coding."


4. REFACTOR KEYWORDS
--------------------
Purpose: Improves EXISTING code without changing behavior.

Keywords:
  • "Refactor this code"
  • "Keep the behavior exactly the same"
  • "Improve readability"
  • "Remove duplication"
  • "Extract helper methods"
  • "Improve naming of variables and methods"
  • "Make it production-ready"

Example:
  "Refactor this code, keep the behavior exactly the same, 
   and improve readability."


5. DEBUGGING KEYWORDS
---------------------
Purpose: Finds and fixes bugs.

Keywords:
  • "Analyze this code for bugs"
  • "Explain why this error might happen"
  • "Walk through the code step by step"
  • "Identify possible root causes"
  • "Propose specific fixes"
  • "Show the corrected code"

Example:
  "Analyze this code for bugs and walk through it step by 
   step, then show the corrected code."


6. TESTING KEYWORDS
-------------------
Purpose: Writes tests for your code.

Keywords:
  • "Write unit tests using JUnit 5"
  • "Add parameterized tests"
  • "Add tests for edge cases"
  • "Use Mockito to mock dependencies"
  • "Cover success and failure scenarios"
  • "Aim for high coverage of branches"

Example:
  "Write unit tests using JUnit 5 and Mockito, covering 
   success, failure, and edge cases."


7. PERFORMANCE KEYWORDS
-----------------------
Purpose: Makes code faster or use less memory.

Keywords:
  • "Optimize for time complexity"
  • "Optimize for memory usage"
  • "Explain the Big-O complexity"
  • "Suggest a more efficient algorithm"
  • "Avoid unnecessary object creation"
  • "Consider large input sizes"

Example:
  "Suggest a more efficient algorithm and explain the 
   Big-O complexity."


8. DOCUMENTATION KEYWORDS
-------------------------
Purpose: Gets explanations, not just code.

Keywords:
  • "Explain this code line by line"
  • "Summarize what this class does"
  • "Add concise comments for non-obvious logic"
  • "Describe the data flow"
  • "Compare this approach with an alternative"

Example:
  "Explain this code line by line and describe the data flow."


==============================================================
                    COPY-PASTE TEMPLATE
==============================================================

Act as a [ROLE].

Here is the problem: [YOUR QUESTION]

Please solve this by:
1. Let's think step by step.
2. Break it down into clear components.
3. Show your work for every step.
4. Therefore, provide the final answer last.


==============================================================
                      QUICK REFERENCE
==============================================================

  GOAL                    KEYWORDS TO USE
  ----                    ---------------
  Better reasoning   -->  "Let's think step by step"
  New code           -->  "Generate code that..."
  Fixed code         -->  "Analyze for bugs, show corrected"
  Cleaner code       -->  "Refactor, keep behavior same"
  Explanations       -->  "Explain line by line"
  Tests              -->  "Write unit tests covering edge cases"
  Performance        -->  "Explain Big-O complexity"


==============================================================
                    LOGIC CONNECTOR WORDS
==============================================================

Use these in your examples to connect thoughts:

  • "Therefore"
  • "Because"
  • "This implies"
  • "Consequently"
  • "First... Then... Finally..."


==============================================================


